---
import Chapter from '../../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Neighborhoods", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Winnetka", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/winnetka"}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Place", "name": "Winnetka, Illinois", "url": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/winnetka", "containedInPlace": {"@type": "Place", "name": "North Shore, Chicago, IL"}}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Winnetka — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="Winnetka village brief — Tudor revival, Georgian colonial, and Prairie School architecture, the corridor's tightest market, anchored by New Trier Township High School District 203."
  path="/neighborhoods/winnetka" current="/neighborhoods" palette="0.15"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "Snapshot"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Architecture"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.15">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Winnetka &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        The <em>tightest</em> market on the corridor.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Winnetka anchors the corridor's middle &mdash; walkable, lakefront, the lowest inventory-to-demand ratio of any North Shore community. Storied homes here move in weeks, not months, and price discovery runs unusually <em>disciplined</em>.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">View the snapshot &darr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/intelligence#ch-02">Open live dashboard</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.40">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">Winnetka Snapshot</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        A village of <em>scarcity</em>, walkability, and lake.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Winnetka's median list price of $2.10M reflects both the architectural pedigree of the building stock and the structural scarcity of available inventory. Days-on-market average just 22 &mdash; among the fastest on the corridor &mdash; and sale-to-list ratios run 99.1%, a signal that well-priced homes transact at or near ask. The price-per-square-foot of $612 is second only to Kenilworth, reflecting the premium attached to walkable, lakefront village character.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Median Price</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$2.10M</span><span class="d">Village-wide list median</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Days on Market</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">22 days</span><span class="d up">Among the corridor's fastest</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">SP/OLP</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">99.1%</span><span class="d up">Sale-to-list ratio</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">$/SqFt</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$612</span><span class="d up">Premium for village character</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="market-blend" style="padding:16px 24px 56px;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;background:#0A1838;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:16px;padding:22px 22px 12px;box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35);">
    <div id="blendedMarket"></div>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.65">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Architecture &amp; Schools</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Layered <em>vocabulary</em>, anchor schools.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Winnetka's building stock layers <strong>Tudor revival, Georgian colonial, and Prairie School</strong> across overlapping eras &mdash; with significant commissions from the early twentieth century preserved alongside meticulous teardown-rebuilds of the last fifteen years. The lakefront blocks east of Sheridan trade at a meaningful premium to the western half of the village, and the inventory-to-demand ratio is the tightest of any North Shore community.
      </p>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Winnetka's K&ndash;8 students attend one of three feeder districts before entering <strong>New Trier Township High School (District 203)</strong> &mdash; the corridor's anchor district and one of the most-cited reasons families relocate from Chicago's North Side. New Trier's academic record, athletic program, and post-secondary placement are central to Winnetka's enduring price strength.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Move in <em>Winnetka</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. We'll walk through what's actually available right now, what's quietly being readied for market, and the three to six month forward view on the village. No pitch.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-block fade-up">
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Direct</div><div class="v"><a href="tel:+18478499828" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">(847) 849-9828</a></div></div>
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Email</div><div class="v"><a href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com</a></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">Schedule the Call &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/neighborhoods">Back to neighborhoods</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(lds[1])} />
  <script slot="scripts" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script slot="scripts" src="/brand/charts/d3-brand.js" is:inline></script>
</Chapter>
